"title": "5575: talk, idle",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5575",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Loose or careless speech, often motivated by curiosity, which can lead to unacceptable consequences. Scripture emphasises the importance of avoiding careless talk, and considering one's words with care.</p>\n<h2>Unfounded boasting is idle talk</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:17-2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:17–2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:3\">PSA 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:6\">PSA 49:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:1\">PSA 52:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:14\">PRO 25:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:1\">PRO 27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9-Acts8:10\">ACT 8:9–8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:16\">JAS 4:16</a></p>\n<h2>Human questioning of God is idle talk</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:20-Rom9:21\">ROM 9:20–9:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:16\">ISA 29:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9\">ISA 45:9</a></p>\n<h2>Flattery is idle talk</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:18\">ROM 16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21\">PRO 7:21</a></p>\n<h2>Meaningless conversation is idle talk</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:11-Job27:12\">JOB 27:11–27:12</a></strong> <em>Job referring to the words of his comforters.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:2\">JOB 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:2\">JOB 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:16\">JOB 35:16</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:14\">PRO 20:14</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of idle talk</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:10-1Kgs20:11\">1KI 20:10–20:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:1-Num12:2\">NUM 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:26-Judg9:41\">JDG 9:26–9:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:41-1Sam17:44\">1SA 17:41–17:44</a></p>\n<h2>Idle talk is folly</h2>\n<h3>A mark of the fool</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:2-Job15:3\">JOB 15:2–15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:3\">PRO 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:23\">PRO 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:12-Eccl10:14\">ECC 10:12–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:6-1Tim1:7\">1TI 1:6–1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Talking too much</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:7\">ECC 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:19\">PRO 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:28\">PRO 17:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:23\">PRO 21:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:3\">ECC 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>Speaking rashly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:25\">PRO 20:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:6\">ECC 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:19\">JAS 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>Idle talk is combated by upright living</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:15\">1PE 2:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Idle talk has no place in the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:20\">1CO 4:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:29\">EPH 4:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:4\">EPH 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:10-Titus1:11\">TIT 1:10–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>All idle talk will be judged</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:36-Matt12:37\">MAT 12:36–12:37</a></strong></p>",
